Spotify has announced that its Premium subscription is available to new subscribers for just R5.99 for their first three months. After the three months are up, users will be billed the standard R59.99 per month. Spotify is an audio streaming service that lets users listen to music and podcasts from a variety of devices, including smartphones, laptops, smart TVs, and smart speakers. This deal is only available to users who have not tried Spotify Premium before â€“ meaning current subscribers cannot take advantage of this deal. Spotify also offers a free version, which includes ads, limited song skips, and no offline listening. This offer ends on 31 December 2018.